<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-03-23"><hi rend="italic">March 23,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of March 19. Colombian minister for foreign affairs says
                            that he believes when the assembly approves the treaty with Panama it
                            will adopt a resolution declaring that “Region of Jurado” does not
                            extend south of Jurado River. He says such a resolution would enormously
                            facilitate Government’s labors to secure approval. Desires your
                            opinion.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>